      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 152: The controller starts in Probing state and immediately increases bitrate on the first non-congested RTCP report. Because setupVideoBitrateInfo() seeds the target from codecVideo-\u003ebitrate, stable calls will drift upward every second until maxBitrate even when the negotiated/default bitrate was intentionally lower. Initialize/reset to Stable after explicit setTargetBitrate(), or only enter Probing after a prior decrease. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nvoid\nBandwidthController::setTargetBitrate(unsigned bitrateKbps)\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(bitrateKbps);\n    lastStableBitrate_ \u003d targetBitrate_;\n    state_ \u003d State::Stable;\n}\n```\nAlso consider reset() using Stable unless recovery probing is explicitly desired.",
