      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 862: delayMonitor() now holds mutex_ while calling socketPair_-\u003ewriteData(). This callback is on the RTP delay path, and doing socket I/O under the session mutex can block other media/session operations or deadlock if writeData triggers code that also needs this mutex. Keep only the shared-state checks/update under the lock, then send the REMB packet outside it. Suggested shape:\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cuint8_t\u003e remb;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    if (!socketPair_)\n        return;\n    ...\n    if (shouldSend) {\n        remb \u003d cc-\u003ecreateREMB(value);\n        lastRembSent_ \u003d now;\n    }\n}\nif (!remb.empty())\n    socketPair_-\u003ewriteData(remb.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(remb.size()));\n```",
